    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "How To Read This Dashboard On First Login",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 45
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### First login notes\\n- Grafana defaults: `admin` / `admin` (local demo).\\n- Monitoring API key is required for `/metrics`, `/alerts`, and `/decision`.\\n- Dashboard refresh is fixed at `30m`.\\n- `external` mode is optional narrative polish; `local` mode remains authoritative for ranking, risk, forecast, and business impact.\\n- In `external` mode, page loads and each refresh cycle can trigger repeated AI-backed narrative requests because multiple panels query `/decision/focus`.\\n- `watch` is predictive guidance, while formal alerts come from `/monitor` threshold breaches."
      }
